description:
Initially debuting in 2008, the ASICS Gel-1130 Black Pure Silver sneakers draw inspiration from the design elements of the GEL-KAYANO 14. This lifestyle running sneaker incorporates a variety of advanced materials to achieve a contemporary look and feel, including technology like GEL cushioning and TRUSSTIC support.

The Black Pure Silver ASICS Gel-1130 features black and pure silver mesh panels, with a logo patch located on the side. It has a rounded toe and employs a front lace-up fastening for secure closure. It also features polished side stripes and a mesh upper. The design is completed with a chunky rubber sole that offers durability and style.

What our experts love about the ASICS Gel-1130 Black Pure Silver is its distinctive retro aesthetics. This sneaker is characterized by its chunky silhouette and the fusion of modern design elements with nostalgic, vintage-inspired style. The sneaker released on 31st May 2023 for $95.

The ASICS Gel-1130 in White Clay Canyon is a shoe with its design inspired by the Gel-KAYANO 14 sneaker, with a similar look and updated technology. The shoe was originally released in 2008 and received a makeover in 2023.

This running shoe is constructed from a mix of synthetic leather and light textile materials that allow for breathability and flexibility. White mesh makes up the base of the shoe, while silver and brown synthetic leather cross on the midsole, creating ASICSâ€™ signature style. The ASICS Gel-1130 sneaker has gel cushioning for comfort and shock absorption. The lining also contains cooling pads to keep your feet from overheating.

What our StockX experts appreciate most about this shoe is its classic colorway. The White Clay Canyon colorway works well to make this unique shoe suitable for wear with any outfit. The ASICS Gel-1130 in White Clay Canyon was first released on July 21st, 2023, at a retail price of $95.

The ASICS Gel-1130 White Pure Silver is a performance running sneaker that finds inspiration in the ninth version of the Gel-1000 and the GEL-KAYANO.

Synthetic overlays in black and metallic Pure Silver replace traditional leather and give the sneaker a contemporary look. The sneaker boasts a mesh upper in white with a loose weave. This loose weave allows the foot to breathe and is lightweight. The bulky midsole features Gel technology in the heel, which delivers responsive cushioning. ASICS, in black lettering, runs diagonally down the tongue and is one of the few visible branding elements. Like other ASICS Gel-1130 models, the White Pure Silver iteration features an adjustable lace closure.

Our experts at StockX like the way the black details on the overlays complement the black tread on the rubber outsole. The ASICS Gel-1130 White Pure Silver was released on February 15, 2024, and retailed at $95.

The Asics Gel Kayano 14 White Midnight W is a sleek and stylish running shoe that offers both comfort and performance. The shoe features a white and midnight colorway that is both eye-catching and versatile. The upper is made of a breathable mesh material that allows for maximum airflow, while the Gel cushioning system in the sole provides excellent shock absorption and support. The Asics Gel Kayano 14 White Midnight W is set to release on February 5th, 2023, with a retail price of $150. This shoe is perfect for runners who want a comfortable and stylish shoe that can keep up with their active lifestyle. Something we love about the Asics Gel Kayano 14 White Midnight W is the combination of style and performance. Our experts think that the standout feature of this shoe is the Gel cushioning system, which provides excellent support and shock absorption. Overall, we love the Asics Gel Kayano 14 White Midnight W for its sleek design, comfortable fit, and excellent performance.

shoeName: ASICS Gel Kayano 14 Arctic Sky Pure Silver

description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 White Cloud Gray is a running shoe inspired by past versions of Gel models, including the Gel-1000 and the Gel-Kayano 14, for a late 2000s running aesthetic.

This iteration of the ASICS Gel-1130 features a white mesh base for the upper, allowing for breathability and flexibility. Synthetic leather overlays appear in the traditional ASICS design in white, black, and Cloud Gray across the midsole. The cushioned tongue features the ASICS logo, while "GEL" can be found running diagonally down the heel in gray and black. Gel technology cushioning and the lining on the inside provide extra comfort and shock absorption.

Our favorite feature of this running shoe is the chunky beige outsole, which adds another touch of modernity and style to the design of the functional shoe. The ASICS Gel-1130 White Cloud Gray was released on March 1, 2024, for a price of $100.

shoeName: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Cream Black Metallic Plum
description:
The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Cream Black Metallic Plum is a running shoe that was released as part of the ASICS Gel-Kayano series.

The upper of the Cream Black Metallic Plum ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 is crafted with a combination of leather and mesh materials, offering both durability and breathability. The shoe comes in a cream-and-black colorway and has a traditional lace-up closure that ensures a snug and secure fit. The outsole features a vertical flex groove that enables the foot to move more naturally, reducing stress on the foot and the potential for injury.

We think that one of the most notable features of the ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Cream Black Metallic Plum is the dynamic DuoMax support system on the sole. This system provides stability and support for the foot, reducing pronation and enhancing the overall efficiency of your stride. The Gel technology used in the heel of the shoe also provides additional cushioning to absorb impact and help prevent injuries and fatigue. The sneaker was released on May 30th, 2023, at a retail price of $150.

The ASICS Gel NYC Graphite Gray Black is an ode to the original model that was initially released in the early 2000s. This pair of shoes mixes retro influences with athleticism.

The Graphite Gray Black ASICS Gel NYC is designed to be a modern running shoe with retro vibes. The upper part of the shoe is based off the original GEL-NIMBUS 3 and contains various embellishments from the MC-PLUS V design. It has a black body that is composed of leather and mesh and features gray overlays. Lightweight foams are used for the base of the shoe to help with cooling.

One feature of this model that our experts particularly like is the gel technology inserts that are included in the midsole that help to provide additional support. The ASICS Gel NYC Graphite Gray Black was first released on April 14th, 2023, for an initial retail price of $130.

The ASICS Gel-1130 White Black is a performance running shoe with a design rooted in the technical running sneakers from the early 2000s.

The "White Black" version of the ASICS Gel-1130 finds inspiration in the GEL-KAYANO 14 and the ninth iteration of the GEL-1000 series. Although the model was first introduced in 2008, this version features an all-white base with black and silver accents. The upper is made of lightweight mesh with a loose weave that gives the sneaker an airy feel. Synthetic leather overlays cross the mesh base and contribute to the shoeâ€™s technical silhouette. In terms of technology, gel cushioning in the heel reduces impact without weighing the shoe down. ASICSâ€™ signature TRUSSTIC support system also improves stability and is a throwback to the early 2000s.

Our StockX experts like the dope-dyed sockliner. This dyeing technique reduces water usage by 33 percent. The ASICS Gel-1130 White Black was released on January 1st, 2024, and retailed at $95.

The ASICS Gel-NYC Oyster Grey features a contemporary oyster grey colour scheme that exudes modern style. Its design is complemented by ASICS' renowned Gel cushioning technology, providing superior comfort and shock absorption.

The NYC Oyster Grey boasts a sleek urban style in a contemporary oyster grey hue. Anchored by ASICS' renowned Gel cushioning technology, the midsole ensures exceptional comfort and impact absorption with every step. The shoe's durable construction and modern design extend to the versatile outsole, enabling seamless transitions between various activities while maintaining a perfect balance of fashion and functionality.

We're particularly enamored by the sneakerâ€™s utilization of their renowned Gel cushioning technology. This innovative feature not only ensures unparalleled comfort but also provides a responsive and supportive feel and is what our experts believe truly sets this shoe apart. The ASICS Gel-NYC Oyster Grey was released on the 14th of April, 2023, and sold for $130.

shoeName: ASICS Gel-NYC Cream Mineral Beige Pink
description:
The ASICS Gel-NYC Cream Mineral Beige Pink is a technical running shoe that finds inspiration in heritage and contemporary ASICS models, including the Gel-Nimbus 3 from the 2000s and the Gel-MC Plus V.

The upper construction of the Cream Mineral Beige Pink ASICS Gel-NYC features breathable mesh with a medium-sized weave in cream and a grid of suede and leather overlays in Mineral Beige and metallic silver across the side panels. Although the upper takes elements from the Gel-Nimbus 3, the midsole combines advanced underfoot technology from the Gel-Cumulus 16. The use of gel inserts in the rear and forefoot as well as a combination of foams creates a responsive feel and protects against impact stress.

Something our experts at StockX love is the pink suede panels that form the mudguard and adorn the toecap area. They complement the pink detailing on the midsole and add a contemporary touch to the sneakerâ€™s retro construction. The ASICS Gel-NYC Cream Mineral Beige Pink was released on May 1, 2024, and retailed at $130.

The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 White Fjord Grey is a premium running shoe that combines style and performance. Featuring a sleek white upper with fjord grey accents, this sneaker offers a clean and versatile look suitable for both athletic pursuits and casual wear. The Gel-Kayano 14 incorporates ASICS' renowned GEL technology in the heel and forefoot, providing superior shock absorption and cushioning for a comfortable stride.

Built with durability and support in mind, the Gel-Kayano 14 boasts a robust construction that caters to various foot types. The engineered mesh upper ensures breathability, while the reinforced heel counter promotes stability during movement. With its blend of cutting-edge technology and timeless design, this shoe is ideal for runners seeking a reliable and stylish option for their daily training or long-distance runs. Our experts state this product is great for athletes looking for a perfect balance of comfort, performance, and aesthetic appeal in their running footwear.

Inspired by the people, culture, and lifestyle of New York City, the ASICS Gel-NYC Cream Cloud Grey dresses the innovative silhouette in a neutral colorway of Cloud Grey and cream.

Originally designed by Angelo Baque, the Cream Cloud Grey ASICS Gel-NYC is a mashup of retro and contemporary influences. For example, the Gel-Nimbus 3 and the Gel-MC Plus V inform the upper, while the tooling system borrows from the Gel Cumulus 16. This gives the sneaker upgraded Gel cushioning in the heel and forefoot but also celebrates running shoes from the early 2000s through the bulky, layered upper. Breathable mesh in Cream makes up the base, while leather and synthetic overlays in Cloud Grey create a supportive, crisscross pattern on the side panels.

Our experts at StockX like the padding around the collar and in the tongue because it adds comfort and contributes to the bulky aesthetic. The ASICS Gel-NYC Cream Cloud Grey was released on July 13, 2024, and sold for $130.

Our experts feel that the best feature of the Gel-1130 Blueberry is its understated aesthetic, which has just the right amount of metallic pop. The ASICS Gel-1130 Cream Blueberry was released on January 1, 2025, and retailed for $95.

The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Black Pure Silver is a running shoe that pays homage to the style of the late 2000s with updated materials and construction.

This version of the ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 is made with a black mesh upper for breathability. Synthetic leather overlays can be seen across the midsole in black and silver forming the classic ASICS design. There are also black overlays around the toebox and heel for extra support. The ASICS logo appears in silver on the cushioned tongue, and GEL branding appears in silver on the heel. The shoe is equipped with a TRUSSTIC support system and trademark Gel cushioning for comfort and shock absorption.

What makes these shoes stand out is the black colorway. The black with a few accents of silver elevates these shoes from a simple running shoe to a stylish fashion choice. The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Black Pure Silver was released on January 1, 2024, for a price of $150.

The ASICS Gel-1130 White Midnight (GS) is a stability running shoe that draws inspiration from the Gel-Kayano series, in particular the Gel-Kayano 14, and the ninth iteration of the GEL-1000 series.

Originally introduced in 2008, the White Midnight (GS) ASICS Gel-1130 features white mesh underlays that provide breathability and create an airy feel. While previous models used genuine leather to create the supportive overlays, this version replaces genuine leather with faux leather. This materials upgrade gives the sneaker a modern look while paying tribute to archived design details. In addition, the sneaker boasts GEL technology in the heel for shock absorption and a TRUSSTIC support system for improved stability.

Our experts at StockX like the Midnight details on the rubber outsole, collar lining, and overlays, which break up the sneakerâ€™s primarily white and silver aesthetic. The grade school-sized ASICS Gel-1130 White Midnight (GS) was released on March 3, 2024, and retailed at $85.
